ing: 2 pounds skinless, boneless chicken thighs, cubed
1 pound turkey sausage, casings removed and crumbled
1 (14.5 ounce) can reduced sodium chicken broth
des: "A healthy alternative to the high-calorie gumbo that will settle your craving without the guilt. Add rice, okra, and shrimp if you like. Serve over cooked brown or white rice."
ins:
Combine chicken thighs, tomatoes, turkey sausage, chicken broth, onion, green bell pepper, garlic, Cajun seasoning, cayenne pepper, and ground black pepper in a slow cooker. Stir together to combine.
Cook on Low until flavors are blended, about 6 hours.
